sub_topic: Prove that the Cartesian product of two sets is not distributive over complement.
message_1: Let A and B be sets defined as A={1,2} and B={a,b,c}. Find the sets (A x B) and (A') x (B') then show that the Cartesian product of two sets is not distributive over complement by proving that (A x B)' is not equal to (A' x B').
